01:01:30,562 --> 01:01:32,314
♪Nevertheless, it's still beautiful, don't you agree?

764
01:01:32,439 --> 01:01:34,733
♪Don't you feel that the dream that

765
01:01:34,858 --> 01:01:37,694
♪you've always wanted to fulfill is tying you down?

766
01:01:37,819 --> 01:01:43,533
♪If I have just the tiniest speck of courage
to say that you can give it up…

767
01:01:43,658 --> 01:01:50,290
♪Let's throw away the bag, pen,
and even the things you really wanted to have

768
01:01:56,588 --> 01:01:58,215
♪And make our way to the town

769
01:01:58,340 --> 01:02:09,142
♪～

770
01:02:09,267 --> 01:02:11,436
♪You threw away the "self"

771
01:02:11,561 --> 01:02:13,563
♪That you wanted to be

772
01:02:13,688 --> 01:02:17,108
♪It was truly precious

773
01:02:17,234 --> 01:02:19,569
♪And yet I only start to remember about it now,
all too late

774
01:02:20,737 --> 01:02:22,405
♪I didn't even realize

775
01:02:22,530 --> 01:02:24,908
♪That the white flower in the vase has withered

776
01:02:25,033 --> 01:02:28,036
♪Even though the truly precious one

777
01:02:28,161 --> 01:02:31,081
♪Was the person who replaces the flower

778
01:02:38,171 --> 01:02:40,382
♪Ah, wait.

779
01:02:44,052 --> 01:02:46,429
♪You're really leaving, aren't you…

780
01:02:48,473 --> 01:02:50,934
♪Is there really no map that shows

781
01:02:51,059 --> 01:02:54,062
♪the details of our long, distant journey ahead?

782
01:02:54,187 --> 01:02:56,231
♪I'm not sure if we wouldn't get lost

783
01:02:56,356 --> 01:02:57,899
♪Well, that's fine.

784
01:02:58,024 --> 01:02:59,526
♪It's fine that way, so…

785
01:02:59,651 --> 01:03:02,195
♪Let's throw away all the things that we actually didn't need,

786
01:03:02,320 --> 01:03:06,408
♪and the sofa and book too

787
01:03:06,533 --> 01:03:08,076
♪Really, it's fine

788
01:03:08,201 --> 01:03:13,540
♪Would there be a dazzling ray of light
that will keep illuminating your night?

789
01:03:13,665 --> 01:03:16,084
♪Would you leave no matter what?

790
01:03:16,209 --> 01:03:17,836
♪Well, that's fine.

791
01:03:17,961 --> 01:03:19,421
♪It's fine that way, so…

792
01:03:19,546 --> 01:03:22,173
♪After you've finished reading everything,

793
01:03:22,299 --> 01:03:25,218
♪please open your eyes

794
01:03:32,475 --> 01:03:37,272
♪Then, let's throw away this book
and make our way to the town

795
01:03:37,397 --> 01:03:48,575
♪～

796
01:04:00,837 --> 01:04:08,011
(Sound of insect wings)

797
01:04:08,136 --> 01:04:09,471
I hear wings.

798
01:04:09,596 --> 01:04:12,265
Something flies in through
the open window.

799
01:04:12,390 --> 01:04:15,977
(Sound of insect wings)

800
01:04:20,690 --> 01:04:22,108
It's a flying insect.

801
01:04:22,233 --> 01:04:26,613
Perhaps a kind of stag beetle.
It has two short pincers.

802
01:04:40,126 --> 01:04:43,922
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

803
01:04:45,465 --> 01:04:48,551
I rush to get my sketchbook.

804
01:04:53,223 --> 01:04:55,809
One night, I see a chameleon.

805
01:04:55,934 --> 01:04:59,562
As I play the piano,
I watch its tail hanging from
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)

806
01:04:59,562 --> 01:04:59,687
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)

807
01:04:59,687 --> 01:05:03,108
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)
the piano top as it swings
in time with the rhythm.

808
01:05:03,108 --> 01:05:03,233
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)

809
01:05:03,233 --> 01:05:06,277
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)
Sometimes,
the tip of its curled tail extends,

810
01:05:06,277 --> 01:05:06,403
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)

811
01:05:06,403 --> 01:05:10,031
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)
and its shadow traces
the black keys of the piano,

812
01:05:10,448 --> 01:05:13,910
swaying back and forth
like the surface of waves.

813
01:05:17,497 --> 01:05:21,000
I'm used to it now.
I don't care what comes anymore.

814
01:05:21,251 --> 01:05:22,919
(Tapping on window)

815
01:05:24,295 --> 01:05:27,924
One night, I hear
the sound of tapping on the window.

816
01:05:28,049 --> 01:05:30,760
It was a beautiful night
with a waning moon.

817
01:05:30,885 --> 01:05:33,096
I listen closely.

818
01:05:33,304 --> 01:05:37,809
There is also a strange sound,
like of a poorly fitted door closing.

819
01:05:37,934 --> 01:05:40,270
(Sound of something creaking)

820
01:05:49,112 --> 01:05:50,780
It's a deer.

821
01:06:09,466 --> 01:06:10,800
It's a deer.

822
01:06:11,009 --> 01:06:13,178
A stag is sitting there.

823
01:06:13,303 --> 01:06:17,015
It's a stag with horns
and a beautiful coat.

824
01:06:17,140 --> 01:06:20,226
It's lying curled up
just outside the window,

825
01:06:20,351 --> 01:06:22,645
lifting its head and looking at me.

826
01:06:22,770 --> 01:06:27,025
I catch a whiff of what I once smelled
in a cowshed on a farm.

827
01:06:27,442 --> 01:06:29,360
(Tapping on the window)

828
01:06:30,570 --> 01:06:33,698
No way. This time it's impossible.

829
01:06:33,948 --> 01:06:35,658
(Tapping on window)

830
01:06:36,367 --> 01:06:38,620
Oh, give me a break.

831
01:06:39,496 --> 01:06:42,165
I can hear the deer's breathing.

832
01:06:43,708 --> 01:06:45,001
(Sigh)

833
01:06:46,336 --> 01:06:47,879
I finally give up,

834
01:06:48,004 --> 01:06:51,299
and back away toward the piano.

835
01:06:51,424 --> 01:06:53,134
I play a single note

836
01:06:53,259 --> 01:06:55,803
and hear that creaking door sound.

837
01:06:55,929 --> 01:06:57,764
(Sound of something creaking)

838
01:06:57,889 --> 01:07:00,850
There's no doubt.
That is the sound it makes.

839
01:07:00,975 --> 01:07:05,688
As if trying to escape reality,
I am impressed by the sound it makes.

840
01:07:06,814 --> 01:07:10,068
I begin playing the introduction,
which I have played often.

841
01:07:12,403 --> 01:07:15,240
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

842
01:07:15,365 --> 01:07:17,992
(Deer's moan)

843
01:07:22,288 --> 01:07:25,708
Please, try to be silent.

844
01:07:26,584 --> 01:07:28,753
(Deer's moan)

845
01:07:30,255 --> 01:07:33,216
Try not to moan.

846
01:07:33,424 --> 01:07:34,801
(Tapping on window)

847
01:07:34,926 --> 01:07:36,427
None of that either.

848
01:07:37,595 --> 01:07:39,264
The deer watches me

849
01:07:39,389 --> 01:07:43,643
with a gaze
that's as black as the deep night,

850
01:07:44,102 --> 01:07:47,188
a mysterious color that draws you in.

851
01:07:51,943 --> 01:08:00,034
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

852
01:08:00,159 --> 01:08:02,453
The deer closes its eyes.

853
01:08:02,579 --> 01:08:06,416
Then it opens and closes
its mouth again and again.

854
01:08:06,874 --> 01:08:08,293
It raises its head

855
01:08:08,418 --> 01:08:11,462
and stretches its nose
as if to approach the window.

856
01:08:11,588 --> 01:08:15,425
Occasionally, its red tongue peeks out.

857
01:08:16,509 --> 01:08:19,220
I can hear the deer's breathing.

858
01:08:19,554 --> 01:08:22,724
For some reason,
the sound has a nostalgic feel.

859
01:08:23,516 --> 01:08:27,562
After finishing the introduction,
I start playing 」Moonlight」 again.

860
01:08:28,146 --> 01:08:33,359
The deer lowers its head back down,
opens its eyes, and looks at me.

861
01:08:35,445 --> 01:08:37,488
This is the only part I can play.

862
01:08:38,865 --> 01:08:41,117
The deer looks at me.

863
01:08:41,242 --> 01:08:43,745
It's as if he's saying, 」That's fine.」

864
01:08:44,203 --> 01:08:47,248
I start playing 」Moonlight」 again.

865
01:08:48,875 --> 01:08:52,503
I play only the introduction,

866
01:08:52,962 --> 01:08:56,174
as if going round and round
in the same place.

867
01:08:59,052 --> 01:09:49,018
(Waves)

868
01:09:49,268 --> 01:10:00,947
(Sound of a toy piano)

869
01:10:01,447 --> 01:10:04,992
(Owl hooting)

870
01:10:05,868 --> 01:10:10,957
I found this on the beach.
Some one must have tossed it out.

871
01:10:11,082 --> 01:10:13,543
It made me wonder

872
01:10:13,668 --> 01:10:17,046
if it would dance
if it wasn't played on my piano.

873
01:10:19,424 --> 01:10:21,884
I see feathers sticking out of the pot.

874
01:10:22,009 --> 01:10:26,931
I bet I'm the only human
who's ever carried an owl in a pot.

875
01:10:27,056 --> 01:10:29,851
It's dark black eyes look at me.

876
01:10:29,976 --> 01:10:34,564
There are yellow circles like egg yolks
covering those black eyes,

877
01:10:34,689 --> 01:10:36,691
like crescent moons.

878
01:10:37,150 --> 01:10:40,778
I open my sketchbook
and start drawing with my pencil.

879
01:10:40,903 --> 01:10:44,949
The owl in the pot stands there
with a puzzled look.

880
01:10:50,997 --> 01:10:55,710
Long ago, I often used to dream of
becoming a bird.

881
01:10:56,669 --> 01:10:59,672
Oh. Not a bird like you.

882
01:11:00,047 --> 01:11:02,717
A bird that spreads its wings wide.

883
01:11:03,593 --> 01:11:07,221
Its wings shining faintly with the dew

884
01:11:07,597 --> 01:11:11,517
that wet its wings
as it flew between the trees.

885
01:11:11,809 --> 01:11:16,439
The sunlight before it has fully risen is
almost annoyingly beautiful.

886
01:11:16,564 --> 01:11:18,483
My body shivers.

887
01:11:20,151 --> 01:11:22,737
Then, I fly

888
01:11:23,404 --> 01:11:25,364
toward the sun.

889
01:11:25,990 --> 01:11:29,410
Eventually, I run out of energy and fall.

890
01:11:30,661 --> 01:11:33,581
When I woke up, I remembered it clearly.

891
01:11:33,706 --> 01:11:36,334
When I drew it on paper,

892
01:11:36,626 --> 01:11:39,545
I got a mysteriously good feeling.

893
01:11:40,797 --> 01:11:45,384
Now that I think about it,
that was the first picture I drew.

894
01:11:45,968 --> 01:11:48,846
(Sound of a toy piano)

895
01:11:51,182 --> 01:11:55,061
I doubt I am any different than then.

896
01:11:55,186 --> 01:11:58,272
Or rather, I have not changed.

897
01:11:58,648 --> 01:12:01,400
I am better at using a brush and pen,

898
01:12:01,526 --> 01:12:03,319
but that is all.

899
01:12:03,444 --> 01:12:07,698
Only my sketching is better.
Only my perspective is more accurate.

900
01:12:07,824 --> 01:12:10,785
Only my lines are more beautiful.

901
01:12:12,537 --> 01:12:16,666
What is in my head, what is before me,

902
01:12:16,791 --> 01:12:19,961
I am merely copying what I see there.

903
01:12:20,169 --> 01:12:22,380
When asked if that's what I want to draw,

904
01:12:22,505 --> 01:12:24,382
I tilt my head.

905
01:12:26,676 --> 01:12:28,344
I am empty.

906
01:12:29,887 --> 01:12:32,056
I sometimes become afraid.

907
01:12:32,932 --> 01:12:36,060
Is what I am doing actually

908
01:12:37,478 --> 01:12:41,190
not much different than
what a camera does?

909
01:12:45,236 --> 01:12:49,866
(Sound of a toy piano)

910
01:12:51,576 --> 01:12:55,538
When I think too much about things
like that, I play this song.

911
01:12:55,913 --> 01:12:59,709
Piano sonata 14, the Moonlight Sonata.

912
01:13:00,001 --> 01:13:01,919
I love this song.

913
01:13:02,044 --> 01:13:04,714
I was taught it when I was a child.

914
01:13:04,839 --> 01:13:09,802
It clearly sounds like a depressing song,
but how can I put this...

915
01:13:11,721 --> 01:13:14,348
Nobody has ever agreed with me on this,

916
01:13:14,473 --> 01:13:17,685
but when I play this, I become incredibly

917
01:13:19,729 --> 01:13:21,689
nostalgic.

918
01:13:28,696 --> 01:13:30,781
My eyes meet the yellow crescent moons.

919
01:13:31,574 --> 01:13:34,577
I don't care and keep playing the keys.

920
01:13:35,119 --> 01:13:37,622
Every time the scratchy sound is played,

921
01:13:37,747 --> 01:13:42,376
I see the owl fluffing its wings
in discomfort.

922
01:13:46,631 --> 01:13:51,636
｢The Fifth Night｣
♪～

923
01:13:51,636 --> 01:17:40,865
♪～

924
01:17:51,542 --> 01:17:56,547
｢Snow Country｣
