01:19:54,999 --> 01:20:08,137
♪Stretching over a dining table and a long bar,
the snow country is

934
01:20:08,804 --> 01:20:19,982
♪just catching the scent of the stillness
of spring star flowers.

935
01:20:21,692 --> 01:20:33,829
♪Your tears scatter in the wind and it's like
we're in the middle of the spring.

936
01:20:36,165 --> 01:20:47,551
♪Sitting in a daze, we're looking at our own reflections
on the surface of the soup.

937
01:20:48,302 --> 01:21:12,993
♪～

938
01:21:13,118 --> 01:21:25,297
♪Our melancholy piles up day after day
and it looks like the snow country.

939
01:21:27,591 --> 01:21:34,348
♪I beg you to hesitate. I hope you care too.

940
01:21:34,473 --> 01:21:39,019
♪Until the snow melts.

941
01:21:41,397 --> 01:21:45,901
♪Until the love is solved.

942
01:21:48,112 --> 01:22:11,677
♪～

943
01:22:12,052 --> 01:22:25,149
♪Coming out of the long tunnel on the border,
we found ourselves

944
01:22:25,816 --> 01:22:37,369
♪taking on the stillness of a bone-chilly night
and tinged with white.

945
01:22:57,139 --> 01:23:00,392
♪～
｢Whale｣

946
01:23:00,392 --> 01:23:00,517
｢Whale｣

947
01:23:00,517 --> 01:23:02,144
｢Whale｣
♪Your pectoral fins

948
01:23:02,144 --> 01:23:06,690
♪Your pectoral fins

949
01:23:06,815 --> 01:23:13,238
♪swim by the window,

950
01:23:13,363 --> 01:23:19,495
♪looking like melted

951
01:23:19,620 --> 01:23:25,000
♪and softened amber.

952
01:23:26,043 --> 01:23:32,341
♪The tip of your nose,

953
01:23:32,508 --> 01:23:38,639
♪your dorsal fin and moustache,

954
01:23:38,764 --> 01:23:45,103
♪and your quiet eyes look like

955
01:23:45,229 --> 01:23:50,984
♪they belong to the night.

956
01:23:51,109 --> 01:23:54,238
♪Talking, crying,

957
01:23:54,363 --> 01:23:57,407
♪we were stroking the waves

958
01:23:57,533 --> 01:24:03,830
♪as if feeling nostalgic for the land.

959
01:24:06,083 --> 01:24:10,963
♪Drop your eyelids and cover your eyes.

960
01:24:11,088 --> 01:24:15,801
♪Sleep tight so that you won't awake right away

961
01:24:15,926 --> 01:24:18,804
♪with your breath spouting out.

962
01:24:18,929 --> 01:24:23,767
♪Now swim deep, swim on

963
01:24:23,892 --> 01:24:29,439
♪in the waves of your shallow sleep

964
01:24:30,023 --> 01:24:34,778
♪falling into a white slumber.

965
01:24:36,446 --> 01:24:42,703
♪Your chirping

966
01:24:42,869 --> 01:24:49,167
♪and dappled sunlight on the sofa

967
01:24:49,293 --> 01:24:55,549
♪remind me of the seashore

968
01:24:55,674 --> 01:25:00,929
♪that swayed softly.

969
01:25:01,471 --> 01:25:04,600
♪Laughing, weeping,

970
01:25:04,725 --> 01:25:07,811
♪we are waiting for the waves

971
01:25:07,936 --> 01:25:14,192
♪so that we can recall before long.

972
01:25:16,528 --> 01:25:21,408
♪Travel through the waves and dive deep,

973
01:25:21,533 --> 01:25:26,121
♪deeper and deeper until you suffocate

974
01:25:26,246 --> 01:25:29,207
♪with your breath spouting out.

975
01:25:29,333 --> 01:25:34,212
♪Now swim deep, swim on

976
01:25:34,338 --> 01:25:40,052
♪with your long tail fin

977
01:25:40,427 --> 01:25:44,514
♪laid down on the waves.

978
01:25:44,640 --> 01:26:08,622
♪～

979
01:26:08,747 --> 01:26:11,792
♪Talking, crying,

980
01:26:11,917 --> 01:26:15,045
♪we were stroking the waves

981
01:26:15,170 --> 01:26:21,259
♪hoping to see each other again someday.

982
01:26:23,637 --> 01:26:28,642
♪Drop your eyelids and cover your eyes.

983
01:26:28,767 --> 01:26:33,021
♪Sleep tight so that you won't awake from a dream

984
01:26:33,146 --> 01:26:36,400
♪and forgive yourself already.

985
01:26:36,525 --> 01:26:41,363
♪Now swim deep, swim on

986
01:26:41,488 --> 01:26:47,077
♪in the waves of your shallow sleep

987
01:26:47,703 --> 01:26:52,833
♪falling into a white slumber.

988
01:26:52,958 --> 01:27:43,884
♪～

989
01:27:51,349 --> 01:27:58,857
(Phone ringing)

990
01:28:01,109 --> 01:28:04,988
Did you see the picture I sent?

991
01:28:05,989 --> 01:28:07,783
What did you think?

992
01:28:09,284 --> 01:28:13,955
Actually, I tried drawing
like you told me before.

993
01:28:14,080 --> 01:28:17,501
When I used those animals
as a motif for my drawings,

994
01:28:17,626 --> 01:28:20,086
it was unbelievably easy to draw them.

995
01:28:20,212 --> 01:28:24,257
This series of pictures
is called 」Dancing Animals.」

996
01:28:24,382 --> 01:28:27,427
I think
they've turned out really interesting.

997
01:28:27,761 --> 01:28:28,970
Yeah.

998
01:28:29,721 --> 01:28:31,014
Uh-huh.

999
01:28:31,264 --> 01:28:33,600
Oh, uh...

1000
01:28:33,725 --> 01:28:37,312
Canary, rabbit, chameleon,

1001
01:28:37,437 --> 01:28:42,067
owl, leaf beetle, frog, bat,

1002
01:28:42,734 --> 01:28:45,237
and the deer.

1003
01:28:45,904 --> 01:28:51,159
Huh? No, seriously.
I was visited by a deer. A stag.

1004
01:28:53,703 --> 01:28:58,500
Yeah, I get it. It sounds unbelievable.

1005
01:28:58,917 --> 01:29:02,128
Yes, the first one is of a human...

1006
01:29:02,254 --> 01:29:05,632
I mean, humans are animals too,
so I just had to draw it.

1007
01:29:05,757 --> 01:29:08,218
The motif?

1008
01:29:08,885 --> 01:29:10,846
Uh, well...

1009
01:29:11,638 --> 01:29:12,848
Yeah?

1010
01:29:13,265 --> 01:29:16,852
Huh? An exhibition?

1011
01:29:18,353 --> 01:29:19,896
Where?

1012
01:29:21,398 --> 01:29:23,692
Oh, there.

1013
01:29:23,984 --> 01:29:26,903
Are you sure? I mean...

1014
01:29:28,071 --> 01:29:30,949
Wait. I'll do it.

1015
01:29:31,950 --> 01:29:34,870
This is a great chance. Sure.

1016
01:29:34,995 --> 01:29:37,455
This makes me so happy. Thank you.

1017
01:29:37,747 --> 01:29:41,459
I'll prep what I've drawn before
so they can be displayed too.

1018
01:29:41,585 --> 01:29:46,756
Sure. Let's meet so we can
talk things over face-to-face.

1019
01:29:47,173 --> 01:29:50,719
Okay. See you later.

1020
01:29:58,226 --> 01:30:00,896
This is a golden opportunity.

1021
01:30:02,981 --> 01:30:04,232
All right.

1022
01:30:09,070 --> 01:30:10,864
Let's do this!

1023
01:30:19,164 --> 01:30:24,169
｢Setting Sun｣
♪Cheeks softly colored by the deep red of the sun

1024
01:30:24,169 --> 01:30:26,296
♪Cheeks softly colored by the deep red of the sun

1025
01:30:26,421 --> 01:30:34,512
♪We shut our eyes in the sunset that burst forth

1026
01:30:34,638 --> 01:30:49,277
♪～

1027
01:30:49,402 --> 01:30:52,948
♪I couldn’t help but be sad

1028
01:30:53,073 --> 01:30:56,785
♪My hands got wet in the sun

1029
01:30:57,285 --> 01:31:00,497
♪Besides, it can’t be helped that it’s radiant

1030
01:31:00,622 --> 01:31:04,376
♪Returning home at a loss for words

1031
01:31:05,752 --> 01:31:12,092
♪Because the red

1032
01:31:15,303 --> 01:31:17,263
♪is glowing as if it were falling,

1033
01:31:17,389 --> 01:31:20,934
♪Just a little longer

1034
01:31:21,059 --> 01:31:26,064
♪Even if I was able to just love myself a little more

1035
01:31:26,731 --> 01:31:32,445
♪When I notice the setting sun,
I can’t keep my eyes open

1036
01:31:36,658 --> 01:31:40,453
♪In the quiet evening calm

1037
01:31:47,460 --> 01:31:50,880
♪I couldn’t help being sad

1038
01:31:51,006 --> 01:31:54,759
♪I touched the sun

1039
01:31:55,260 --> 01:31:58,680
♪It seems to burn weakly

1040
01:31:58,805 --> 01:32:02,642
♪It barely charred my fingertips

1041
01:32:02,976 --> 01:32:06,396
♪The grapes seemed to have grown too high

1042
01:32:06,521 --> 01:32:10,316
♪For me to reach, so I stopped trying

1043
01:32:10,775 --> 01:32:14,112
♪I wonder if I’ve fallen in love

1044
01:32:14,237 --> 01:32:17,907
♪Just like the sun,

1045
01:32:19,242 --> 01:32:26,875
♪I’m falling even though there’s no reason to yet.

1046
01:32:28,752 --> 01:32:33,965
♪(I'd rather—)

1047
01:32:34,090 --> 01:32:46,436
♪～

1048
01:32:46,561 --> 01:32:53,401
♪Cheeks softly colored by the deep red of the sun

1049
01:32:53,526 --> 01:33:05,622
♪If the sunset bursting across the sky just illuminates our path

1050
01:33:05,747 --> 01:33:14,422
♪In a little while, I will be able to love myself

1051
01:33:15,256 --> 01:33:21,054
♪I saw that shy you in the setting sun

1052
01:33:25,016 --> 01:33:28,728
♪In the quiet evening calm

1053
01:33:32,941 --> 01:33:36,778
♪As we closed our eyes

1054
01:33:49,624 --> 01:33:54,629
｢Fireworks of Shoes｣
♪～

1055
01:33:54,629 --> 01:33:57,382
♪～

1056
01:33:57,507 --> 01:33:59,384
♪Look, look,

1057
01:33:59,509 --> 01:34:05,431
♪I don’t have the words to say anything

1058
01:34:05,557 --> 01:34:11,938
♪Because, because I’ve been left open-mouthed

1059
01:34:13,606 --> 01:34:15,024
♪(So—)

1060
01:34:15,150 --> 01:34:29,455
♪～

1061
01:34:29,581 --> 01:34:31,374
♪Look, look,

1062
01:34:31,499 --> 01:34:37,338
♪Even if I stay silent, words aren’t necessary

1063
01:34:37,463 --> 01:34:42,177
♪Because my eyes will speak for me

1064
01:34:44,596 --> 01:34:52,562
♪Forgetting is a fruit that bugs have begun to eat

1065
01:34:52,687 --> 01:35:00,111
♪All that remains in my memory is an always-smiling face

1066
01:35:00,236 --> 01:35:04,282
♪As I’m flying through the twilight-colored sky,

1067
01:35:04,407 --> 01:35:08,286
♪Even shooting through the atmosphere,

1068
01:35:08,411 --> 01:35:13,208
♪Below me, rapidly growing small,

1069
01:35:13,333 --> 01:35:16,252
♪Is the town where you were

1070
01:35:16,377 --> 01:35:20,131
♪Beneath my shoes, flowers bloomed

1071
01:35:20,256 --> 01:35:24,177
♪Giant flowers of fire bloomed

1072
01:35:24,302 --> 01:35:30,642
♪“I’ll leave behind everything that’s in my heart,”
I think

1073
01:35:30,767 --> 01:35:34,687
♪That’s the kind of summer I could see

1074
01:35:34,812 --> 01:35:49,285
♪～

1075
01:35:49,619 --> 01:35:51,412
♪Look, look,

1076
01:35:51,537 --> 01:35:57,210
♪Even if I try to get to know you, it’s ambiguous

1077
01:35:57,543 --> 01:36:02,215
♪Because you’re full of pride

1078
01:36:05,593 --> 01:36:13,351
♪There’s nothing that can make me feel refreshed

1079
01:36:13,476 --> 01:36:18,606
♪But the sky is beautiful again today

1080
01:36:20,483 --> 01:36:28,533
♪I’m sure that everything I’ve eaten is a compensation paid to life

1081
01:36:28,658 --> 01:36:36,165
♪I’m too late, and now I can’t even become a nighthawk

1082
01:36:36,291 --> 01:36:40,128
♪Dancing in the dawn-colored sky

1083
01:36:40,253 --> 01:36:44,173
♪“What do you wish for?” is such a foolish question

1084
01:36:44,299 --> 01:36:47,969
♪I grew up and forgot about it

1085
01:36:48,094 --> 01:36:52,181
♪That you’re reflected in my eyes is such a nuisance

1086
01:36:52,307 --> 01:36:56,227
♪Flowers were always ringing out beneath me

1087
01:36:56,352 --> 01:37:00,189
♪Giant flowers of fire were ringing out

1088
01:37:00,315 --> 01:37:06,571
♪“The noise alone makes me cry,”
I think

1089
01:37:06,696 --> 01:37:11,117
♪That’s the kind of summer I heard

1090
01:37:11,242 --> 01:37:41,397
♪～

1091
01:37:41,522 --> 01:37:43,232
♪Look, look,

1092
01:37:43,358 --> 01:37:49,364
♪Even if I fly in the sky, there’s no end to it

1093
01:37:49,489 --> 01:37:56,079
♪Because I’ll surely end up searching for you

1094
01:37:57,497 --> 01:37:58,956
♪(So—)

1095
01:38:00,249 --> 01:38:04,128
♪As I’m flying in the twilight-colored sky,

1096
01:38:04,253 --> 01:38:08,049
♪Breaking free of even the present of this planet,

1097
01:38:08,174 --> 01:38:11,677
♪Below me, rapidly growing small

1098
01:38:11,803 --> 01:38:16,182
♪And then disappearing, is the town where you were

1099
01:38:16,307 --> 01:38:20,311
♪In the summer sky, flowers bloomed

1100
01:38:20,436 --> 01:38:24,107
♪Giant flowers of fire bloomed

1101
01:38:24,232 --> 01:38:30,655
♪“I want to keep crying forever,”
I think

1102
01:38:30,780 --> 01:38:35,284
♪That’s the kind of summer that vanished

1103
01:38:35,410 --> 01:38:50,800
♪～

1104
01:39:07,358 --> 01:39:11,279
Okay. I see.

1105
01:39:12,029 --> 01:39:15,741
Yes. I'll be careful.

1106
01:39:16,325 --> 01:39:18,244
Thank you always.

1107
01:39:18,494 --> 01:39:21,289
The exhibition? It's coming soon.

1108
01:39:21,414 --> 01:39:25,585
As a sign of gratitude, as my landlord,
can I invite you?

1109
01:39:25,918 --> 01:39:30,506
Oh, I see. Ha ha ha...
No, it's okay.

1110
01:39:30,631 --> 01:39:33,009
Yes. Okay.

1111
01:39:34,093 --> 01:39:35,428
Goodbye.

1112
01:39:40,641 --> 01:39:43,769
It's not easy living in this day and age.

1113
01:39:46,105 --> 01:39:48,816
Seems like I haven't painted for days.

1114
01:39:48,941 --> 01:39:51,736
Probably because I've been busy prepping.

1115
01:39:52,028 --> 01:39:53,237
(Cat meowing)

1116
01:39:53,446 --> 01:39:56,032
I hear a cat meowing somewhere.

1117
01:39:56,157 --> 01:39:58,242
I open the window and look outside.

1118
01:39:58,618 --> 01:40:00,161
Nothing there.

1119
01:40:00,286 --> 01:40:01,537
Oh well, whatever.

1120
01:40:01,662 --> 01:40:05,333
I leave the window open
and sit at the piano.

1121
01:40:06,918 --> 01:40:08,377
I touch the keys.

1122
01:40:08,503 --> 01:40:11,547
I begin playing the intro
to 」Moonlight.」

1123
01:40:12,381 --> 01:40:19,055
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

1124
01:40:20,598 --> 01:40:25,269
After playing a while,
I hear something at the window.

1125
01:40:25,686 --> 01:40:29,982
A cat suddenly appears
and sits on the piano.

1126
01:40:30,650 --> 01:40:33,694
I watch the cat as I continue playing.

1127
01:40:34,237 --> 01:40:37,907
The cat raises its nose
into the air and stands up.

1128
01:40:38,699 --> 01:40:43,246
It closes its eyes,
as if listening to the notes.

1129
01:40:44,288 --> 01:40:46,249
I stop playing.

1130
01:40:46,374 --> 01:40:48,543
The cat stops moving.

1131
01:40:49,335 --> 01:40:53,422
It opens its eyes
and I see the tips of its hair moving.

1132
01:40:58,219 --> 01:41:00,471
I've been drawing pictures of you.

1133
01:41:00,596 --> 01:41:02,890
All of these here.

1134
01:41:03,015 --> 01:41:05,643
They're pretty fun, right?

1135
01:41:06,394 --> 01:41:10,940
I guess the landlord must have seen me.

1136
01:41:11,315 --> 01:41:14,569
He said he thought I'd been feeding
the animals.

1137
01:41:14,694 --> 01:41:16,946
When I told him the animals came

1138
01:41:17,071 --> 01:41:19,657
simply because I was playing the piano,

1139
01:41:19,782 --> 01:41:22,451
he looked at me as if I was mad.

1140
01:41:23,411 --> 01:41:27,873
So he told me he's taking back
the piano at the end of the month.

1141
01:41:28,457 --> 01:41:31,377
This belongs to the landlord.

1142
01:41:31,627 --> 01:41:34,839
His niece wants to learn,
so he's giving it to her.

1143
01:41:34,964 --> 01:41:39,135
Mind you, I'm sure there were
complaints about the noise, too.

1144
01:41:40,845 --> 01:41:44,557
This piano is going to disappear.

1145
01:41:46,267 --> 01:41:51,314
That means there's no reason
for you guys to keep coming.

1146
01:41:54,233 --> 01:41:59,196
I don't like it.
You're not disposable materials.

1147
01:42:00,072 --> 01:42:02,283
It's thanks to you, I made this art,

1148
01:42:02,408 --> 01:42:05,202
and I've been able to do
a solo exhibition.

1149
01:42:05,494 --> 01:42:07,955
I mean, you guys,

1150
01:42:08,080 --> 01:42:10,249
you come here to hear me play, right?

1151
01:42:10,666 --> 01:42:23,971
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

1152
01:42:24,096 --> 01:42:27,725
The eyes of the cat sitting on
the piano meet mine.

1153
01:42:29,226 --> 01:42:31,312
I'm stunned.

1154
01:42:33,064 --> 01:42:37,568
The cats' eyes are
the color of the deep night.

1155
01:42:39,654 --> 01:42:44,283
They shimmer like the surface of water.

1156
01:42:47,036 --> 01:42:50,247
I feel as if I've seen this color before.

1157
01:42:52,291 --> 01:42:54,377
Sometime, long, long ago.

1158
01:42:55,670 --> 01:42:59,173
Somewhere.

1159
01:43:02,301 --> 01:43:03,803
What is this?

1160
01:43:05,763 --> 01:43:08,599
I felt something running down on my face.

1161
01:43:09,016 --> 01:43:10,893
(Sniffling)

1162
01:43:13,646 --> 01:43:15,064
Tears.

1163
01:43:17,566 --> 01:43:19,610
Overflowing tears.

1164
01:43:23,489 --> 01:43:26,867
The image of me
desperately wiping away my tears

1165
01:43:26,992 --> 01:43:29,537
can be seen in the mirror in the room.

1166
01:43:30,413 --> 01:43:33,833
The moonlight
gently illuminates the piano keys.

1167
01:43:34,542 --> 01:43:37,169
The cat quietly approaches me.

1168
01:43:37,670 --> 01:43:43,217
Then it puts its nose
against mine as if to kiss me.

1169
01:43:44,969 --> 01:43:49,598
The cat silently goes out the window.

1170
01:43:51,809 --> 01:43:58,441
This was the last time I ever saw them.

1171
01:44:14,206 --> 01:44:19,211
｢Left-Right Confusion｣
♪You're poking my cheeks with your right hand

1172
01:44:19,211 --> 01:44:20,463
♪You're poking my cheeks with your right hand

1173
01:44:20,755 --> 01:44:25,301
♪While I'm holding a warm mug with my left hand

1174
01:44:26,719 --> 01:44:33,142
♪Your right eyebrow looks a little droopy

1175
01:44:33,267 --> 01:44:37,438
♪It's hard to believe how many mornings have arrived

1176
01:44:39,064 --> 01:44:40,566
♪I'm content with just one thing

1177
01:44:40,691 --> 01:44:43,736
♪Just one peony whose flowers never fall

1178
01:44:43,861 --> 01:44:45,946
♪A happiness that touches you,

1179
01:44:46,071 --> 01:44:51,494
♪And makes you forget even your heart

1180
01:44:51,619 --> 01:44:53,245
♪Really, I'm fine with just one thing

1181
01:44:53,370 --> 01:45:04,131
♪A night so dark and deep you can't tell left from right

1182
01:45:04,548 --> 01:45:10,513
♪The stillness of going on a journey alone

1183
01:45:10,638 --> 01:45:16,727
♪If I could convey to you even one of these things…

1184
01:45:17,478 --> 01:45:23,859
♪Your left eyebrow looks a little droopy

1185
01:45:23,984 --> 01:45:26,862
♪I just can't seem to remember

1186
01:45:27,154 --> 01:45:30,074
♪It feels like I just never knew

1187
01:45:30,199 --> 01:45:36,163
♪About the novel you bought one day that you had in your right hand

1188
01:45:36,413 --> 01:45:42,503
♪Wait, maybe it was in your left hand…?

1189
01:45:42,628 --> 01:45:48,259
♪～

1190
01:45:48,467 --> 01:45:50,261
♪I'm content with just one thing

1191
01:45:50,386 --> 01:45:53,180
♪Just one ray of sunshine that shines through the night

1192
01:45:53,305 --> 01:45:55,516
♪A sentimentality that would touch you

1193
01:45:55,641 --> 01:46:00,938
♪and open your heart and let me see through it

1194
01:46:01,063 --> 01:46:02,523
♪Really, I'm fine with just one thing

1195
01:46:02,648 --> 01:46:13,784
♪Like the fact that you can move forward
even during a fluttering summer hailstorm if you just feel your way through

1196
01:46:13,909 --> 01:46:20,207
♪Or that your eyes won't close

1197
01:46:21,083 --> 01:46:32,928
♪～

1198
01:46:33,053 --> 01:46:40,686
♪I would tear off my heart from my body, little by little,

1199
01:46:40,811 --> 01:46:42,354
♪And hand it to you.

1200
01:46:42,479 --> 01:46:45,357
♪I will give my everything to you, so…

1201
01:46:45,482 --> 01:46:48,444
♪I will give you the ruby from the hilt of my sword,

1202
01:46:48,903 --> 01:46:52,156
♪and the sapphires from my eyes

1203
01:46:52,406 --> 01:46:58,162
♪And I will put my heart of lead beside you

1204
01:47:01,123 --> 01:47:02,666
♪I'm content with just one thing

1205
01:47:02,791 --> 01:47:05,836
♪Just one peony whose flowers never falls

1206
01:47:05,961 --> 01:47:08,047
♪A happiness that touches you,

1207
01:47:08,172 --> 01:47:13,510
♪And makes you forget even your tears

1208
01:47:13,636 --> 01:47:15,346
♪I'm fine with just a little bit 

1209
01:47:15,471 --> 01:47:23,062
♪A bit of the sun to stop today’s light rain

1210
01:47:26,398 --> 01:47:27,942
♪Just a little bit,

1211
01:47:28,067 --> 01:47:33,447
♪Let me leave just a little bit of my footprints in your world

1212
01:47:33,572 --> 01:47:38,869
♪Do you understand? That your happiness

1213
01:47:38,994 --> 01:47:40,663
♪Isn't confined to just one thing

1214
01:47:40,788 --> 01:47:51,632
♪A night so dark and deep you can't tell left from right

1215
01:47:51,757 --> 01:47:57,596
♪The long journey you will embark on from now on

1216
01:47:58,138 --> 01:48:04,228
♪The fact that I'm the only one that doesn’t smile

1217
01:48:04,561 --> 01:48:10,526
♪If I could convey to you even just one of them…

1218
01:48:14,279 --> 01:48:20,661
♪I can't taste anything no matter what I eat

1219
01:48:20,786 --> 01:48:25,249
♪It feels like I've lost my body

1220
01:48:26,667 --> 01:48:33,090
♪I believed

1221
01:48:33,215 --> 01:48:38,220
♪That your heart and mine would always be one

1222
01:48:48,313 --> 01:48:53,318
｢Spring Thief｣
♪～

1223
01:48:53,318 --> 01:49:19,053
♪～

1224
01:49:19,178 --> 01:49:26,060
♪When I crossed the elevated bridge,
I could see the blue sky peeking through the clouds

1225
01:49:26,810 --> 01:49:33,275
♪It's really hot lately,
so I was just waiting for a breeze

1226
01:49:34,234 --> 01:49:37,196
♪Sitting beneath the shade of a tree,

1227
01:49:38,030 --> 01:49:40,407
♪There's something stuck on my cheeks

1228
01:49:41,992 --> 01:49:46,789
♪When I look up, flowers are blooming and falling right above my head

1229
01:49:49,166 --> 01:49:53,087
♪Gently falling, we're now forgetting to even breathe

1230
01:49:53,212 --> 01:49:56,924
♪And it's too much work to even blink

1231
01:49:57,049 --> 01:50:01,136
♪Well, even today will turn into the past tomorrow

1232
01:50:01,261 --> 01:50:04,431
♪So I'm just waiting for the wind

1233
01:50:04,556 --> 01:50:08,519
♪That's why, we're now forgetting even our voices

1234
01:50:08,644 --> 01:50:12,272
♪And it's too much work to even say goodbye

1235
01:50:12,397 --> 01:50:17,152
♪Flowers are just falling beneath the sunny sky

1236
01:50:17,277 --> 01:50:20,197
♪Right now, a spring storm is happening

1237
01:50:20,322 --> 01:50:35,838
♪～

1238
01:50:35,963 --> 01:50:38,423
♪The next day, I met up with you again at the same place

1239
01:50:39,925 --> 01:50:42,928
♪There weren't that many people who went to see the cherry blossoms anymore

1240
01:50:43,554 --> 01:50:46,265
♪And I couldn't smell spring in the air anymore

1241
01:50:47,474 --> 01:50:50,185
♪I guess summer will come again this year

1242
01:50:51,311 --> 01:50:58,235
♪When I crossed the elevated bridge,
I could see you peeking from the end of the road

1243
01:50:58,944 --> 01:51:01,613
♪I wonder how much time is left?

1244
01:51:02,990 --> 01:51:05,409
♪I wonder how many more times can I still meet you in the spring...

1245
01:51:06,451 --> 01:51:09,079
♪At the hill by the riverside,

1246
01:51:10,289 --> 01:51:13,083
♪we're sitting beneath the shade of a tree

1247
01:51:14,084 --> 01:51:21,842
♪Again, just like yesterday, beneath the blooming flowers,

1248
01:51:21,967 --> 01:51:25,345
♪We're now forgetting to even breathe,

1249
01:51:25,470 --> 01:51:28,932
♪And it's too much work to even blink

1250
01:51:29,057 --> 01:51:33,145
♪There's no mistaking it; this storm of flowers scattering about right now

1251
01:51:33,270 --> 01:51:36,481
♪Is the spring thief

1252
01:51:36,732 --> 01:51:40,819
♪Today, still, time is being carried away by the wind,

1253
01:51:40,944 --> 01:51:44,531
♪And it's too much work to even stand up

1254
01:51:44,656 --> 01:51:49,244
♪The sky can be seen between the falling flowers

1255
01:51:49,369 --> 01:51:52,206
♪A spring storm is happening, still

1256
01:51:52,331 --> 01:52:07,930
♪～

1257
01:52:08,055 --> 01:52:10,515
♪Today, I'll go to see you as well

1258
01:52:11,683 --> 01:52:14,269
♪Then I'll sit beneath the shade of a tree

1259
01:52:15,479 --> 01:52:17,981
♪And let out a sigh

1260
01:52:19,399 --> 01:52:22,027
♪The flowers have stopped blooming

1261
01:52:23,445 --> 01:52:25,781
♪I'll go to see you again tomorrow

1262
01:52:27,032 --> 01:52:29,868
♪Spring is coming to an end

1263
01:52:30,869 --> 01:52:35,999
♪Time is fluttering down as if it's leaving behind
traces of the days we spent together

1264
01:52:38,961 --> 01:52:42,089
♪There aren't enough words out there to sing of love

1265
01:52:42,214 --> 01:52:45,717
♪It's too much work to even make them rhyme

1266
01:52:45,842 --> 01:52:53,475
♪There's no way things like words can convey the blossoming present

1267
01:52:53,600 --> 01:52:57,479
♪Gently falling, we're now forgetting even our voices

1268
01:52:57,604 --> 01:53:01,316
♪And it's too much work to even blink

1269
01:53:01,441 --> 01:53:04,820
♪Only the two of us are here to watch the cherry blossoms

1270
01:53:05,237 --> 01:53:08,907
♪And I'm begging for the spring storm to not stop just yet

1271
01:53:09,032 --> 01:53:12,661
♪Just a little bit left

1272
01:53:12,786 --> 01:53:16,373
♪I can now count the ones left

1273
01:53:24,631 --> 01:53:28,010
♪Two flowers left

1274
01:53:32,139 --> 01:53:35,559
♪Just one more flower left

1275
01:53:39,771 --> 01:53:44,526
♪Only the leaves are left now, gently falling

1276
01:53:44,651 --> 01:53:47,654
♪Right now, spring has come to an end

1277
01:53:58,040 --> 01:54:03,045
｢Algernon｣
♪～

1278
01:54:03,045 --> 01:54:35,494
♪～

1279
01:54:38,330 --> 01:55:30,715
♪～

1280
01:55:31,466 --> 01:55:37,931
♪Why did you give me my heart?

1281
01:55:38,056 --> 01:55:43,895
♪Why did you paint my eyes?

1282
01:55:44,729 --> 01:55:51,403
♪Greater than the sky,
swallowing the winds that sweeps away the clouds

1283
01:55:51,528 --> 01:55:57,159
♪My eyes are seeing a dream once again

1284
01:55:59,035 --> 01:56:04,082
♪Still on barefoot…

1285
01:56:08,295 --> 01:56:14,885
♪You're slowly changing, ever so slightly

1286
01:56:15,010 --> 01:56:21,516
♪As if watching a loaf of bread gradually puff up

1287
01:56:21,641 --> 01:56:25,729
♪You're slowly running

1288
01:56:25,854 --> 01:56:34,988
♪Staying unafraid of the long maze ahead

1289
01:56:36,490 --> 01:56:42,913
♪Why did you give me my name?

1290
01:56:43,205 --> 01:56:48,793
♪Why did you make me my hands?

1291
01:56:49,920 --> 01:56:56,176
♪Bigger than the sea,
swallowing the waves that even washes away the sand

1292
01:56:56,426 --> 01:57:02,098
♪These little hands were still staring far off into the distance

1293
01:57:02,265 --> 01:57:07,437
♪A single yawn…

1294
01:57:11,608 --> 01:57:15,737
♪We're slowly falling asleep

1295
01:57:15,862 --> 01:57:18,156
♪For a very long time,

1296
01:57:18,281 --> 01:57:24,913
♪in the center of our minds, a large tree grows

1297
01:57:25,038 --> 01:57:29,125
♪We're slowly walking through the roots

1298
01:57:29,251 --> 01:57:38,301
♪So that we won't be afraid of the long maze ahead

1299
01:57:38,593 --> 01:57:44,516
♪I wonder if one day I'll ever meet the person
that I've always struggled to catch up with

1300
01:57:45,392 --> 01:57:51,189
♪I wonder if one day I'll freeze up
behind a wall that I couldn't get past

1301
01:57:52,023 --> 01:57:57,904
♪I wonder if one day you'll end up giving up as well

1302
01:57:59,322 --> 01:58:02,409
♪You're slowly changing

1303
01:58:02,534 --> 01:58:05,829
♪You're slowly changing

1304
01:58:05,954 --> 01:58:08,248
♪You're slowly changing...

1305
01:58:08,373 --> 01:58:14,879
♪We're slowly forgetting, ever so slightly

1306
01:58:15,005 --> 01:58:21,553
♪As if staring at a tower slowly crumbling

1307
01:58:21,678 --> 01:58:25,807
♪We're slowly falling asleep

1308
01:58:25,932 --> 01:58:29,144
♪Slowly falling asleep…

1309
01:58:31,688 --> 01:58:38,278
♪You're slowly changing, ever so slightly

1310
01:58:38,403 --> 01:58:44,909
♪As if you're a shade growing in the middle of that tree

1311
01:58:45,035 --> 01:58:49,080
♪You're slowly running

1312
01:58:49,205 --> 01:58:58,214
♪Staying unafraid of the long maze ahead

1313
01:58:58,923 --> 01:59:05,513
♪While certainly being lost in it.

1314
01:59:05,639 --> 02:00:45,739
♪～

1315
02:01:16,060 --> 02:01:18,438
This is a series of pictures

1316
02:01:18,563 --> 02:01:21,983
of mysterious animals
that visted my home.

1317
02:01:22,192 --> 02:01:25,862
After midnight,
they would sit near my piano

1318
02:01:25,987 --> 02:01:28,072
and dance strange dances.

1319
02:01:28,198 --> 02:01:31,868
There was a mysterious charm to them.

1320
02:01:32,243 --> 02:01:36,372
They inspired me to create
this series of ten paintings.

1321
02:01:36,498 --> 02:01:39,793
I certainly hope that you enjoy them.

1322
02:01:43,880 --> 02:01:47,175
It was time for my exhibition.

1323
02:01:47,383 --> 02:01:49,928
I have a small sheet of paper in my hands.

1324
02:01:50,094 --> 02:01:54,015
It's a small postcard-size sheet
outlining the solo exhibition.

1325
02:01:54,140 --> 02:01:57,435
There were a few people
inside the small exhibition space

1326
02:01:57,560 --> 02:01:59,729
in a renovated room of a building.

1327
02:01:59,854 --> 02:02:03,566
Still, I feel
a strange sense of satisfaction.

1328
02:02:05,235 --> 02:02:06,528
Hello.

1329
02:02:06,653 --> 02:02:09,322
Well, if it isn't my landlord.

1330
02:02:09,447 --> 02:02:12,867
I see you've come. Thank you.

1331
02:02:12,992 --> 02:02:15,703
Please, enjoy.

1332
02:02:16,496 --> 02:02:18,373
(Woman) May I have one?

1333
02:02:18,873 --> 02:02:20,750
I hear a voice.

1334
02:02:21,626 --> 02:02:24,128
I see a once familiar face.

1335
02:02:24,629 --> 02:02:29,092
She's the girlfriend
I broke up with a while back.

1336
02:02:30,677 --> 02:02:36,474
Nice to see you. I appreciate
all your help with this.

1337
02:02:36,599 --> 02:02:37,809
(Ex-girlfriend) No problem.

1338
02:02:37,934 --> 02:02:41,771
The pictures are good.
I just wanted to lend you a hand.

1339
02:02:42,814 --> 02:02:45,859
You seem pretty busy lately.

1340
02:02:45,984 --> 02:02:47,026
(Ex-girlfriend) Yes.

1341
02:02:47,151 --> 02:02:51,281
Since I plan exhibitions while working,
I don't have much time.

1342
02:02:51,406 --> 02:02:55,034
But I enjoy it. It's what I want to do.

1343
02:02:55,326 --> 02:02:59,789
I stop myself before saying,
」You haven't changed.」

1344
02:03:00,498 --> 02:03:04,669
People seem as if they haven't changed,
but everyone changes.

1345
02:03:04,794 --> 02:03:07,630
Time doesn't pass only for me.

1346
02:03:08,089 --> 02:03:13,595
She looks at the paper in her left
hand,while my eyes are glued

1347
02:03:13,928 --> 02:03:16,347
to the ring on her ring finger.

1348
02:03:17,682 --> 02:03:22,145
Well, anyway... Enjoy.

1349
02:03:22,270 --> 02:03:27,150
(Ex-girlfriend) Yes. I'm hoping
this will be a good exhibition for you.

1350
02:03:29,903 --> 02:03:33,114
There's nothing special
I can say about the exhibition.

1351
02:03:33,239 --> 02:03:37,577
It lasted for a few weeks
and ended without incident.

1352
02:03:37,702 --> 02:03:42,123
One big development was that offers
were made on some of the paintings.

1353
02:03:42,248 --> 02:03:48,254
After much deliberation,
I kept the cat picture, and sold the rest.

1354
02:03:52,216 --> 02:03:53,635
(Ex-girlfriend) Nice work.

1355
02:03:53,968 --> 02:03:55,803
Oh, thank you.

1356
02:03:55,929 --> 02:03:58,431
(Ex-girlfriend) How was the exhibition?

1357
02:03:58,681 --> 02:03:59,849
It was great.

1358
02:03:59,974 --> 02:04:03,186
It's good to hear people's
reactions in person.

1359
02:04:03,311 --> 02:04:05,438
And I think I made some connections.

1360
02:04:05,563 --> 02:04:08,775
But best of all,
I got a job offer to paint.

1361
02:04:08,900 --> 02:04:11,402
After seeing this, they wanted to work with me.

1362
02:04:11,527 --> 02:04:12,445
(Ex-girlfriend) Really?

1363
02:04:12,570 --> 02:04:14,656
And I sold several paintings.

1364
02:04:14,781 --> 02:04:17,200
Not just of the dancing animals,

1365
02:04:17,325 --> 02:04:19,661
but some of my old paintings too.

1366
02:04:19,786 --> 02:04:21,329
(Ex-girlfriend) That's fantastic!

1367
02:04:21,454 --> 02:04:23,289
I told you about them before.

1368
02:04:23,414 --> 02:04:26,918
They're based on dreams of scenes
from a previous life.

1369
02:04:27,043 --> 02:04:29,837
Remember? You said you didn't like them.

1370
02:04:29,963 --> 02:04:31,214
(Ex-girlfriend) I remember those.

1371
02:04:31,339 --> 02:04:34,926
But that's not what I meant
when I said that.

1372
02:04:35,051 --> 02:04:38,388
I never said that I didn't like them.

1373
02:04:39,013 --> 02:04:39,931
Huh?

1374
02:04:40,056 --> 02:04:42,308
(Ex-girlfriend)
I just said they were dull.

1375
02:04:42,433 --> 02:04:45,728
I said, for a picture to be
accessible to people,

1376
02:04:45,853 --> 02:04:49,190
it's better if there's something
interesting about it.

1377
02:04:49,315 --> 02:04:54,070
Being dull doesn't affect
the quality of the painting.

1378
02:04:54,195 --> 02:04:56,614
Even if the setting's commonplace,

1379
02:04:56,739 --> 02:05:00,284
the painting will still have its own
unique value.

1380
02:05:00,410 --> 02:05:04,163
Even paintings
nobody buys are great paintings.

1381
02:05:07,583 --> 02:05:11,546
Come to think of it, she's probably right.

1382
02:05:12,839 --> 02:05:15,466
Painting is my livelihood,

1383
02:05:15,758 --> 02:05:19,679
so she was just giving me some
helpful advice.

1384
02:05:19,929 --> 02:05:23,182
She wasn't judging me.

1385
02:05:24,225 --> 02:05:27,020
What was it that possessed me?

1386
02:05:28,646 --> 02:05:33,067
That's a great thought.
Who said it? It really encouraged me.

1387
02:05:33,192 --> 02:05:35,028
(Ex-girlfriend) You said it.

1388
02:05:35,778 --> 02:05:38,698
Have you forgotten what you once said?

1389
02:05:40,491 --> 02:05:42,493
You haven't changed a bit.

1390
02:05:45,413 --> 02:05:47,665
I'm at a loss for words.

1391
02:05:48,583 --> 02:05:51,461
Bathed in the evening light
streaming in through the window,

1392
02:05:51,586 --> 02:05:54,255
she laughs mischievously.

1393
02:05:55,214 --> 02:05:59,260
The ring on her ring finger sparkles.

1394
02:06:03,556 --> 02:06:05,683
(Ex-girlfriend)
We'll say bye here. Thank you.

1395
02:06:05,808 --> 02:06:08,978
Okay. I've got to get back
to clean up anyway.

1396
02:06:09,103 --> 02:06:10,104
(Ex-girlfriend)
Hang in there.

1397
02:06:10,229 --> 02:06:12,648
I'll send you the final paperwork later.

1398
02:06:12,774 --> 02:06:13,816
Okay.

1399
02:06:13,941 --> 02:06:16,778
(Ex-girlfriend)
So, are you glad you did it?

1400
02:06:19,781 --> 02:06:21,324
It really feels like

1401
02:06:21,741 --> 02:06:25,078
these are my first
interesting paintings in a while.

1402
02:06:25,453 --> 02:06:29,791
I've gotten work too.
My future seems bright.

1403
02:06:30,750 --> 02:06:35,004
It's all thanks to those animals.

1404
02:06:35,671 --> 02:06:39,300
(Ex-girlfriend) You're so deadpan,
I can't tell when you're kidding.

1405
02:06:39,425 --> 02:06:41,594
Oh, sorry.

1406
02:06:41,719 --> 02:06:44,055
(Ex-girlfriend) I think it's
a great concept though.

1407
02:06:44,180 --> 02:06:46,641
Animals are cute and accessible.

1408
02:06:46,766 --> 02:06:50,436
The paintings had a coherent theme
and were easy on the eyes.

1409
02:06:50,561 --> 02:06:53,731
And it was quite amusing, too.

1410
02:06:53,856 --> 02:06:54,857
What was?

1411
02:06:54,982 --> 02:06:58,778
(Ex-girlfriend) Those animals
kind of resemble you.

1412
02:06:58,903 --> 02:07:01,948
Really?
Do I look that much like an animal?

1413
02:07:02,073 --> 02:07:07,703
How can I phrase it? Your expressions,
your mannerisms. Your aura.

1414
02:07:08,329 --> 02:07:10,748
Like that cat.

1415
02:07:10,873 --> 02:07:13,835
It looks just like you
when you play the piano.

1416
02:07:14,502 --> 02:07:19,841
Eyes closed, looking upward
with your nose poking into the air.

1417
02:07:23,386 --> 02:07:24,887
The piano?

1418
02:07:25,930 --> 02:07:28,349
(Ex-girlfriend) Yes. The piano.

1419
02:07:49,370 --> 02:07:51,873
Dancing animals...

1420
02:07:55,293 --> 02:07:58,254
This is a series of paintings

1421
02:07:58,921 --> 02:08:03,092
of mysterious animals
that visted my home.

1422
02:08:04,302 --> 02:08:09,599
After midnight,
they would sit near my piano

1423
02:08:10,099 --> 02:08:13,186
and dance a strange dance.

1424
02:08:16,898 --> 02:08:19,066
A strange dance...

1425
02:08:25,781 --> 02:08:28,201
A strange dance...

1426
02:08:36,959 --> 02:08:40,796
A strange dance...

1427
02:08:43,674 --> 02:08:47,595
It looks just like you
when you play the piano...

1428
02:08:57,563 --> 02:08:59,732
(Piano plays)

1429
02:09:08,032 --> 02:09:11,702
No, maybe it's the other way around.

1430
02:09:12,703 --> 02:09:14,956
Was I mistaken?

1431
02:09:16,082 --> 02:09:19,669
They weren't dancing.

1432
02:09:20,628 --> 02:09:26,008
Maybe they wanted to play the piano...

1433
02:09:26,592 --> 02:09:37,853
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

1434
02:09:37,979 --> 02:09:40,314
I stand before the piano.

1435
02:09:40,815 --> 02:09:43,818
Moonlight illuminates the piano keys.

1436
02:09:44,193 --> 02:09:48,197
As I look at myself in the mirror
out of the side of my eye,

1437
02:09:48,364 --> 02:09:51,450
I slowly lower my arms to play.

1438
02:09:52,618 --> 02:09:55,329
That melody I have played many times,

1439
02:09:55,788 --> 02:10:00,001
Beethoven's Piano Sonata No. 14.

1440
02:10:01,252 --> 02:10:03,838
I see myself in the mirror.

1441
02:10:04,505 --> 02:10:08,050
My body moves as I play the piano keys.

1442
02:10:08,426 --> 02:10:14,807
And it looks as if I'm dancing
a strange dance.

1443
02:10:16,434 --> 02:11:17,578
♪～

1444
02:11:24,210 --> 02:15:02,011
♪～

